  "text": "The scheduler framework plugin extension points are defined in a clear layered architecture:\n\n1. **Interface definitions** (`pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go`): All 9 plugin interfaces (PreFilterPlugin, FilterPlugin, PreScorePlugin, ScorePlugin, ReservePlugin, PermitPlugin, PreBindPlugin, BindPlugin, PostBindPlugin) are defined here as Go interfaces, each embedding the base `Plugin` interface.\n\n2. **Runtime framework** (`pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go`): The `frameworkImpl` struct holds slices for each plugin type (e.g., `preFilterPlugins []framework.PreFilterPlugin`). The `getExtensionPoints()` method maps config plugin sets to these slices. Run methods (e.g., `RunPreFilterPlugins`, `RunFilterPlugins`) iterate over registered plugins at each extension point.\n\n3. **Registry** (`pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go`): Defines the `Registry` type (`map[string]PluginFactory`) and `PluginFactory` for plugin construction.\n\n4. **In-tree plugin registration** (`pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go`): `NewInTreeRegistry()` registers all built-in scheduler plugins (noderesources, tainttoleration, volumebinding, defaultbinder, etc.) into the runtime Registry.\n\n5. **Plugin names** (`pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/names/names.go`): String constants for all built-in plugin names.\n\n6. **Config types** (`pkg/scheduler/apis/config/types.go`): The `Plugins` struct defines `PluginSet` fields for each extension point (PreFilter, Filter, PreScore, Score, Reserve, Permit, PreBind, Bind, PostBind, plus MultiPoint).\n\n7. **Default plugins** (`pkg/scheduler/apis/config/v1/default_plugins.go`): `getDefaultPlugins()` configures which plugins are enabled by default via MultiPoint.\n\n8. **Instrumented plugins** (`pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/instrumented_plugins.go`): Metric-instrumented wrappers for filter/prefilter plugins.",
